Polyacetylene is an unsaturated compound with a carbon-carbon triple bond. Polyacetylene is one of the active ingredients of PQR. So far, a total of 15 polyacetylene have been reported in PQR, such as acetylpan axydol, (6R, 7S)-6, 7-epoxyte-tradeca-1,3-diyne, falcalinol, ginsenoyne G, heptadeca-1,8-diene-4,6-diyne-3,10-diol, panaxydol, panaxytriol, panaquinquecols I1, panaquinquecols I2, panaquinquecols I3, PQ-1, PQ-2, PQ-3, PQ-7, PQ-1, PQ-8 (
 Fujimoto et al., 1991; 
 Fujimoto et al., 1994; 
 Satoh et al., 1997; 
 Bao et al., 1998).
